snippet.textDisplay:
I must be the only one who wasn't scared of keiths rage outburst? Lol it was kinda funny, and I guess i felt a little uncomfortable for the judges (only because it was dragged out for a minute), but I know it was likely a skit for the show. The only thing that makes me wonder is if keith is genuinely raging or just acting, because his face turns very red. When I see his face turn so red it looks genuine, and makes me think hes actually lashing out.



BUT im gonna lean towards it being a skit, and him forcing himself to be angry for the sake of the joke. I thought it was somewhat funny so Im not complaining ;)


On another note: Keith's dad likes flavors that I find unappealing, so each time I see "daddys favorite", I assume hes gonna come third or fourth place right off the bat (unless zak does something weird like usual). Because raisin brand tastes kinda "meh" and i find it unappealing. Nothing exciting about it can be done really, so while I love his message, I think he should actually try to win the competition instead of just making everything taste like cinnamon raisins all the time. I geniunely think Keith could come second place (after Ned) if he tried, instead of the daddys favorite skit.
